tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned the main form layout and intro section, polished UI components, and
  applied consistent styling across all questionnaire sections, also fixing a
  console error related to null input values.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app from a generic look to a more professional and calming
  aesthetic. I began by analyzing the existing CSS and component styling,
  identifying areas like the color palette, layout, and form elements as needing
  significant improvement. The approach involved implementing a new sleep-themed
  color palette with deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, along with custom
  utility classes for gradients and shadows. I then redesigned the main
  questionnaire form layout, including a new progress indicator and card styling
  with subtle background patterns. The intro section was transformed into a more
  engaging hero experience with feature cards. All core UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were polished with improved hover and
  selected states. Furthermore, all questionnaire sections were updated to use
  consistent, card-like groupings, replacing the previous plain gray boxes.
  During the process, a console error related to  values being passed to
  input components was identified and fixed by ensuring  is converted to
  an empty string. The final steps involved further refining alert colors to
  align with the new theme and increasing the border opacity of section
  groupings for better visual definition.
